                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17180110-25-off127 t17180110-25-cd128"></join> last. The Evidence depos'd the Prisoner came to the Rose and Crown Inn , in St, John's Street , and lodged there 3 or 4 Nights; but he giving them reason to suspect his Honesty, was deny'd longer Entertainment; and the next Morning was apprehended by the Watch, with the Goods upon him: To whom after several improbable pretences, he told where he had them; upon which they went to the Prosecutors House, and acquainting them, the Chamberlain went up and found 3 Beds stripped. The Prisoner for all that deny'd the fact, and said they were given him by a Man and Woman with a Lanthorn, to carry into Southwark , but could not prove it; the Jury therefore though they <rs id="t17180110-25-verdict129" type="verdictDescription">
